docs.abstract: Footage from security cameras and bystanders suggested the officers had lied about the beating, bolstering critics of a new bill that would restrict circulating videos of security forces.
docs.snippet: Footage from security cameras and bystanders suggested the officers had lied about the beating, bolstering critics of a new bill that would restrict circulating videos of security forces.
docs.lead_paragraph: PARIS — Video of police officers beating a Black man in Paris caused an outcry in France on Thursday, fueling criticism of a new bill that would place restrictions on sharing footage of security forces as the French authorities grapple with longstanding accusations of police racism and brutality.

headline.main: Video of Police Beating Black Man in Paris Fuels Debate on Filming Officers
headline.print_headline: French Fiercely Debate  Sharing Videos of Police

docs.abstract: The president and his allies have united right-wing media and internet trolls with false messaging that legitimate vote counting should stop.

docs.lead_paragraph: A disinformation push to subvert the election is well underway, and it is coming straight from President Trump and his allies. The goal: to somehow stop a victory by former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr., or, failing that, undermine his legitimacy before he can take office.
